    33 const d = new Date()
    34 d.setDate(d.getDate() - maxDaysInPast)
    35 const min = `${d.getMonth() + 1}-${d.getDate()}-${d.getFullYear()}`

    37 }

    39 const d = new Date()

    41 const max = `${d.getMonth() + 1}-${d.getDate()}-${d.getFullYear()}`
    42 schema = schema.max(max)
    43 }
    44 return { [this.name]: schema }
    45 }
    46
    47 getFormDataFromState (state) {
    48
    const name = this.name
    49 const value = state[name]
    50 const dateValue = new Date(value)
    51

    52
    [`${name}__day`]:
    value

    dateValue.getDate(),
    53

    57
    58 getStateValueFromValidForm (payload) {
    59 // Use `moment` to parse the date as
    60 // opposed to the Date constructor.
    61 // `moment` will check that the individual date
    62 // parts together constitute a valid date.
    63 // E.g. 31 November is not a valid date
    64
    const name = this.name
    65 return payload[`${name}__year`]
    66 ? moment([
    67 payload[`${name}__year`],
    68 payload[`${name}__month`] - 1,
    69 payload[`${name}__day`]
    70 ]).toDate()
    71 : null
    72 }
    73
    74 getDisplayStringFromState (state) {
    75

    76 const value = state[name]
    77 return value ? moment(value).format('D MMMM YYYY') : ''
    78 }

    217 addConditionalComponents (item, itemModel, formData, errors) {
    218 // The gov.uk design system Nunjucks examples for conditional reveal reference variables from macros. There does not appear to
    219 // to be a way to do this in JavaScript. As such, render the conditional components with Nunjucks before the main view is rendered.
    220 // The conditional html tag used by the gov.uk design system macro will reference HTML rarther than one or more additional
    221 // gov.uk design system macros.
    222
    if (item.conditional) {
    223 itemModel.conditional = {
    224 html: nunjucks.render('conditional-components.html', {
    225 components: item.conditional.componentCollection.getViewModel(
    226 formData,
    227 errors
    228 )
    229 })
    230 }
    231
    }
    232 return itemModel
    233 }

    324 [getSchemaKeys] (schemaType) {
    325
    const schemaName = `${schemaType}Schema`
    326 const schemaKeysFunctionName = `get${schemaType
    327 .substring(0, 1)
    328 .toUpperCase()}${schemaType.substring(1)}SchemaKeys`
    329 const filteredItems = this.items.filter(
    330 item => item.conditional && item.conditional.componentCollection
    331 )
    332 const conditionalName = this.name
    333 const schemaKeys = { [conditionalName]: this[schemaName] }
    334 const schema = this[schemaName]
    335 // All conditional component values are submitted regardless of their visibilty.
    336 // As such create Joi validation rules such that:
    337 // a) When a conditional component is visible it is required.
    338 // b) When a conditional component is not visible it is optional.
    339
    filteredItems.forEach(item => {
    340
    const conditionalSchemaKeys = item.conditional.componentCollection[
    341 schemaKeysFunctionName
    342 ]()
    343 // Iterate through the set of components handled by conditional reveal adding Joi validation rules
    344 // based on whether or not the component controlling the conditional reveal is selected.
    345 Object.keys(conditionalSchemaKeys).forEach(key => {
    346
    Object.assign(schemaKeys, {
    347 [key]: joi.alternatives().when(conditionalName, {
    348 is: item.value,
    349 then: conditionalSchemaKeys[key].required(),
    350 // If multiple checkboxes are selected their values will be held in an array. In this
    351 // case conditionally revealed content is required to be entered if the controlliing
    352 // checkbox value is a member of the array of selected checkbox values.
    353 otherwise: joi.alternatives().when(conditionalName, {
    354 is: joi
    355 .array()
    356 .items(schema.only(item.value), joi.any())
    357 .required(),
    358 then: conditionalSchemaKeys[key].required(),
    359 otherwise: conditionalSchemaKeys[key]
    360 .optional()
    361 .allow('')
    362 .allow(null)
    363 })
    364 })
    365 })
    366 })
    367 })
    368 return schemaKeys
    369 }
    370 }

    232 class ConditionalFormComponent extends FormComponent { 204
    233 constructor(def, model) { 205
    234
    super(def, model);
    		 206
    235 const { 207
    236 options 207
    237 } = this; 207
    238 const list = model.lists.find(list => list.name === options.list); 208
    239 const items = list.items; 209
    240 const values = items.map(item => item.value); 210
    241 this.list = list; 211
    242 this.items = items; 212
    243 this.values = values; 213
    244 this[createConditionalComponents](def, model); 214
    245 } 215
    246
    247 addConditionalComponents(item, itemModel, formData, errors) { 217
    248 // The gov.uk design system Nunjucks examples for conditional reveal reference variables from macros. There does not appear to 218
    249 // to be a way to do this in JavaScript. As such, render the conditional components with Nunjucks before the main view is rendered. 219
    250 // The conditional html tag used by the gov.uk design system macro will reference HTML rarther than one or more additional 220
    251 // gov.uk design system macros. 221
    252
    if (item.conditional) {
    		 222
    253 itemModel.conditional = { 223
    254 html: nunjucks.render('conditional-components.html', { 224
    255 components: item.conditional.componentCollection.getViewModel(formData, errors) 225
    256 }) 224
    257 }; 223
    258
    }
    		 231
    259
    260 return itemModel; 232
    261 } 233
    262
    263 getFormDataFromState(state) { 235
    264
    const formData = super.getFormDataFromState(state);
    		 236
    265
    266 if (formData) { 237
    267 const itemsWithConditionalComponents = this.list.items.filter(item => item.conditional && item.conditional.components); 238
    268 itemsWithConditionalComponents.forEach(item => { 241
    269
    const itemFormDataFromState = item.conditional.componentCollection.getFormDataFromState(state);
    		 242
    270
    271 if (itemFormDataFromState && Object.keys(itemFormDataFromState).length > 0) { 248
    272 Object.assign(formData, itemFormDataFromState); 249
    273 } 250
    274 }); 241
    275 } 252
    276
    277 return formData; 253
    278 } 254
    279
    280 getFormSchemaKeys() { 256
    281
    return this[getSchemaKeys]('form');
    		 257
    282 } 258
    283
    284 getStateFromValidForm(payload) { 260
    285
    const state = super.getStateFromValidForm(payload);
    		 261
    286 const itemsWithConditionalComponents = this.list.items.filter(item => item.conditional && item.conditional.components); 262
    287 const selectedItemsWithConditionalComponents = itemsWithConditionalComponents.filter(item => { 267
    288
    if (payload[this.name] && Array.isArray(payload[this.name])) {
    		 268
    289 return payload[this.name].find(nestedItem => item.value === nestedItem); 269
    290 } else { 272
    291 return item.value === payload[this.name]; 273
    292
    }
    		 274
    293 }); // Add selected form data associated with conditionally revealed content to the state. 278
    294
    295 selectedItemsWithConditionalComponents.forEach(item => Object.assign(state, item.conditional.componentCollection.getStateFromValidForm(payload))); // Add null values to the state for unselected form data associated with conditionally revealed content. 286
    296 // This will allow changes in the visibility of onditionally revealed content to be reflected in state correctly. 287
    297
    298 const unselectedItemsWithConditionalComponents = itemsWithConditionalComponents.filter(item => !selectedItemsWithConditionalComponents.includes(item)); 288
    299 unselectedItemsWithConditionalComponents.forEach(item => { 291
    300
    const stateFromValidForm = item.conditional.componentCollection.getStateFromValidForm(payload);
    		 292
    301 Object.values(item.conditional.componentCollection.items).filter(conditionalItem => stateFromValidForm[conditionalItem.name]).forEach(key => { 297
    302
    const conditionalItemToNull = key.name;
    		 298
    303 Object.assign(stateFromValidForm, { 299
    304 [conditionalItemToNull]: null 299
    305 }); 299
    306 }); 295
    307 Object.assign(state, stateFromValidForm); 301
    308 }); 291
    309 return state; 303
    310 } 304
    311
    312 getStateSchemaKeys() { 306
    313
    return this[getSchemaKeys]('state');
    		 307
    314 } 308
    315
    316 [createConditionalComponents](def, model) { 310
    317
    const filteredItems = this.list.items.filter(item => item.conditional && item.conditional.components);
    // Create a collection of conditional components that can be converted to a view model and rendered by Nunjucks
    		 314
    318 // before primary view model rendering takes place. 315
    319
    320 filteredItems.map(item => { 316
    321
    item.conditional.componentCollection = new ComponentCollection(item.conditional.components, model);
    		 317
    322 }); 316
    323 } 322
    324
    325 [getSchemaKeys](schemaType) { 324
    326
    const schemaName = `${schemaType}Schema`;
    		 325
    327 const schemaKeysFunctionName = `get${schemaType.substring(0, 1).toUpperCase()}${schemaType.substring(1)}SchemaKeys`; 326
    328 const filteredItems = this.items.filter(item => item.conditional && item.conditional.componentCollection); 329
    329 const conditionalName = this.name; 332
    330 const schemaKeys = { 333
    331 [conditionalName]: this[schemaName] 333
    332 }; 333
    333 const schema = this[schemaName]; // All conditional component values are submitted regardless of their visibilty. 335
    334 // As such create Joi validation rules such that: 336
    335 // a) When a conditional component is visible it is required. 337
    336 // b) When a conditional component is not visible it is optional. 338
    337
    338 filteredItems.forEach(item => { 339
    339
    const conditionalSchemaKeys = item.conditional.componentCollection[schemaKeysFunctionName]();
    // Iterate through the set of components handled by conditional reveal adding Joi validation rules
    		 343
    340 // based on whether or not the component controlling the conditional reveal is selected. 344
    341
    342 Object.keys(conditionalSchemaKeys).forEach(key => { 345
    343
    Object.assign(schemaKeys, {
    		 346
    344 [key]: joi.alternatives().when(conditionalName, { 347
    345 is: item.value, 347
    346 then: conditionalSchemaKeys[key].required(), 347
    347 // If multiple checkboxes are selected their values will be held in an array. In this 350
    348 // case conditionally revealed content is required to be entered if the controlliing 351
    349 // checkbox value is a member of the array of selected checkbox values. 352
    350 otherwise: joi.alternatives().when(conditionalName, { 353
    351 is: joi.array().items(schema.only(item.value), joi.any()).required(), 353
    352 then: conditionalSchemaKeys[key].required(), 353
    353 otherwise: conditionalSchemaKeys[key].optional().allow('').allow(null) 359
    354 }) 353
    355 }) 347
    356
    });
    		 346
    357 }); 345
    358 }); 339
    359 return schemaKeys; 368
    360 } 369
    361
    362 } 204

    364 class ComponentCollection { 372

    368 16 return new Type(def, model); 376
    369 }); 374
    370 4 const formItems = itemTypes.filter(component => component.isFormComponent); 379
    371 4 this.items = itemTypes; 381
    372 4 this.formItems = formItems; 382
    373 4 this.formSchema = joi.object().keys(this.getFormSchemaKeys()).required().keys({ 386
    374 crumb: joi.string().optional().allow('') 386
    375 }); 383
    376 4 this.stateSchema = joi.object().keys(this.getStateSchemaKeys()).required(); 388
    377 } 392

    379 getFormSchemaKeys() { 394
    380 const keys = {}; 395
    381 4 this.formItems.forEach(item => { 397

    383 }); 397
    384 4 return keys; 401
    385 } 402
    386
    387 getStateSchemaKeys() { 404
    388 const keys = {}; 405
    389 4 this.formItems.forEach(item => { 407
    390 Object.assign(keys, item.getStateSchemaKeys()); 408
    391 }); 407
    392 4 return keys; 411
    393 } 412
